a-smaller-than-usual-blue-moon-will-end-the-month-with-a-lunar-spectacle-heres-what-to-know-about-the-full-micromoon-180988854/</guid></item><item><title>这位有影响力的超现实主义艺术家和女权主义者不仅仅是缪斯，在新的传记片和艺术展览中得到了应有的回报</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/leonora-carrington-is-no-mere-muse-this-influential-surrealist-artist-and-feminist-gets-her-due-in-a-new-biopic-and-art-exhibitions-180988844/</link><description>新电影《晨光中的利奥诺拉》颂扬了利奥诺拉·卡林顿的生活和工作。与此同时，弗洛伊德博物馆的一个展览首次展示了她在精神病院内创作的艺术品</description><pubDate>Thu, 28 May 2026 19:26:51 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/leonora-carrington-is-no-mere-muse-this-influential-surrealist-artist-and-feminist-gets-her-due-in-a-new-biopic-and-art-exhibitions-180988844/</guid></item><item><title>研究称，随着气候变化，巨大的、破坏性的冰雹变得越来越常见</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/giant-destructive-hail-is-becoming-more-common-with-climate-change-study-says-180988849/</link><description>随着大气变暖，出现像柚子那么大的冰雹的可能性正在增加</description><pubDate>Thu, 28 May 2026 19:02:02 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/giant-destructive-hail-is-becoming-more-common-with-climate-change-study-says-180988849/</guid></item><item><title>在数百人进行恢复仪式的帮助下，英格兰最著名的裸体巨人将再次发出白色光芒</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/englands-most-famous-naked-giant-will-glow-white-again-thanks-to-help-from-hundreds-of-people-performing-a-ritual-of-restoration-180988848/</link><description>英格兰南部 180 英尺高的 Cerne Abbas 巨人正在涂上一层新的粉笔</description><pubDate>Thu, 28 May 2026 18:09:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/englands-most-famous-naked-giant-will-glow-white-again-thanks-to-help-from-hundreds-of-people-performing-a-ritual-of-restoration-180988848/</guid></item><item><title>切萨皮克湾的年轻蓝蟹多年来一直在神秘地减少。今年冬天，他们的人数有所增加。是什么推动了这些趋势？</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/young-blue-crabs-have-been-mysteriously-dwindling-in-the-chesapeake-bay-for-years-this-winter-they-saw-a-boost-in-numbers-whats-driving-these-trends-180988839/</link><description>最近的一份报告详细介绍了自 2010 年以来幼年切萨皮克蓝蟹数量减少了 50%。然后，一项调查发现今年幼年甲壳类动物数量惊人地激增</description><pubDate>Thu, 28 May 2026 15:10:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/young-blue-crabs-have-been-mysteriously-dwindling-in-the-chesapeake-bay-for-years-this-winter-they-saw-a-boost-in-numbers-whats-driving-these-trends-180988839/</guid></item><item><title>你如何纪念倒下的树？在英国，一座声音雕塑将播放哈德良长城附近倒下的心爱梧桐树的“声音”</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-do-you-honor-a-fallen-tree-in-england-a-sound-sculpture-will-broadcast-the-voice-of-a-beloved-sycamore-felled-near-hadrians-wall-180988832/</link><description>“人民之树”还将把这棵树的木材和公众的档案记录融入一系列社区艺术作品中</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 20:51:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-do-you-honor-a-fallen-tree-in-england-a-sound-sculpture-will-broadcast-the-voice-of-a-beloved-sycamore-felled-near-hadrians-wall-180988832/</guid></item><item><title>美国宇航局公布了有关未来月球基地和为其建设奠定基础的任务的新细节</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasa-unveils-new-details-about-the-future-moon-base-and-the-missions-laying-the-groundwork-to-build-it-180988837/</link><description>前三个任务计划于今年发射。它们将涉及由包括蓝色起源在内的多家航空航天公司开发的月球着陆器，并运送科学仪器和月球车</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 20:47:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasa-unveils-new-details-about-the-future-moon-base-and-the-missions-laying-the-groundwork-to-build-it-180988837/</guid></item><item><title>欣赏令人惊叹的中世纪手稿，讲述亚瑟王的故事，以墨水和抛光黄金制成，即将拍卖</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-medieval-manuscript-telling-tales-of-king-arthur-in-ink-and-polished-gold-thats-headed-to-auction-180988835/</link><description>该手稿由一位技艺精湛的匿名艺术家于 1290 年至 1310 年间创作。它是仅有的三份私人拥有的通俗圣经循环手稿中最古老的一份</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 19:29:28 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-medieval-manuscript-telling-tales-of-king-arthur-in-ink-and-polished-gold-thats-headed-to-auction-180988835/</guid></item><item><title>1776 年，愤怒的纽约人怀着革命热情推倒了乔治三世的雕像。新展览让你也能做到</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-1776-angry-new-yorkers-tore-down-a-statue-of-george-iii-with-a-revolutionary-fervor-a-new-exhibition-lets-you-do-it-too-180988830/</link><description>纽约市在美国革命中发挥了关键作用。该博物馆通过文物、沉浸式环境和互动体验生动地展现了这座城市 18 世纪的历史</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 19:00:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-1776-angry-new-yorkers-tore-down-a-statue-of-george-iii-with-a-revolutionary-fervor-a-new-exhibition-lets-you-do-it-too-180988830/</guid></item><item><title>隐藏在林肯纪念堂下方的一座光彩夺目的新博物馆即将向公众开放。这是您可以期待的</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-illuminating-new-museum-hidden-beneath-the-lincoln-memorial-is-set-to-open-to-the-public-heres-what-you-can-expect-180988831/</link><description>林肯纪念堂地下博物馆的门票现已开放预订。当该景点于 6 月 25 日开放时，游客将从全新的角度欣赏这座华盛顿特区的地标建筑</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 17:21:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-illuminating-new-museum-hidden-beneath-the-lincoln-memorial-is-set-to-open-to-the-public-heres-what-you-can-expect-180988831/</guid></item><item><title>科学家利用人工智能重新设计微生物的机器，使其在没有生命关键成分的情况下也能发挥作用</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-used-ai-to-redesign-a-microbes-machinery-to-function-without-a-key-ingredient-of-life-180988802/</link><description>尽管研究人员并没有创造出在没有关键构件的情况下也能发挥作用的完整细胞，但这些发现代表了合成生物学的一大进步，并让人们了解地球上最早的生物体可能是如何生活的。</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 15:46:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-used-ai-to-redesign-a-microbes-machinery-to-function-without-a-key-ingredient-of-life-180988802/</guid></item><item><title>长腿爸爸似乎在南美狩猎青蛙，揭示了细长的蜘蛛类动物是被忽视的掠食者</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/daddy-longlegs-seem-to-hunt-frogs-in-south-america-revealing-the-gangly-arachnids-as-long-overlooked-predators-180988810/</link><description>一项新的研究表明，收割者会主动攻击这些滑溜溜的两栖动物，而不仅仅是吃它们的食物。研究结果表明，这种无脊椎生物与脊椎动物的关系比之前想象的更为复杂</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 13:00:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/daddy-longlegs-seem-to-hunt-frogs-in-south-america-revealing-the-gangly-arachnids-as-long-overlooked-predators-180988810/</guid></item><item><title>沉船，但使其时尚：研究人员将 17 世纪沉船的木质碎片改造成一双时尚的长裙</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-shipwreck-but-make-it-fashion-researchers-transformed-wooden-fragments-from-a-17th-century-shipwreck-into-a-pair-of-stylish-maxi-dresses-180988825/</link><description>芬兰阿尔托大学的科学家保存了 Hahtiperä 残骸碎片并将其转化为纺织纤维</description><pubDate>Tue, 26 May 2026 21:20:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-shipwreck-but-make-it-fashion-researchers-transformed-wooden-fragments-from-a-17th-century-shipwreck-into-a-pair-of-stylish-maxi-dresses-180988825/</guid></item><item><title>得益于水中的 DNA，科学家在西澳大利亚附近发现了一种难以捉摸的巨型乌贼和许多其他令人惊讶的海洋动物</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-detect-an-elusive-giant-squid-and-many-other-surprising-marine-animals-off-western-australia-thanks-to-dna-in-the-water-180988812/</link><description>粘液、粪便、皮肤和其他脱落的组织使研究人员能够调查哪些生物在两个深海峡谷中游泳，而无需观察或捕捉它们</description><pubDate>Tue, 26 May 2026 20:31:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-detect-an-elusive-giant-squid-and-many-other-surprising-marine-animals-off-western-australia-thanks-to-dna-in-the-water-180988812/</guid></item><item><title>考古学家和志愿者利用史前工具和技术建造了一座具有 4,500 年历史的新石器时代大厅复制品，在巨石阵中拔地而起</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-4500-year-old-neolithic-hall-replica-rises-at-stonehenge-as-archaeologists-and-volunteers-build-with-prehistoric-tools-and-techniques-180988806/</link><description>一座史前建筑的重建，最初可能是附近杜灵顿墙遗址冬季盛宴的场所，将作为学生的学习空间</description><pubDate>Tue, 26 May 2026 20:29:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-4500-year-old-neolithic-hall-replica-rises-at-stonehenge-as-archaeologists-and-volunteers-build-with-prehistoric-tools-and-techniques-180988806/</guid></item><item><title>一场突然的山体滑坡引发了阿拉斯加 2025 年的“特大海啸”。现在，科学家们已经确定了预测类似事件的警告信号</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-sudden-landslide-triggered-alaskas-2025-mega-tsunami-now-scientists-have-identified-warning-signs-to-predict-similar-events-180988797/</link><description>研究人员表示，随着气候变化改变了寒冷的地貌，朱诺以南约 45 英里处的特雷西阿姆峡湾发生的自然灾害可能会变得更加常见</description><pubDate>Tue, 26 May 2026 18:23:43 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-sudden-landslide-triggered-alaskas-2025-mega-tsunami-now-scientists-have-identified-warning-signs-to-predict-similar-events-180988797/</guid></item><item><title>惠斯勒无意让他哀悼的母亲成为艺术界明星。今天，她成为伦敦大型展览的亮点</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/whistler-didnt-mean-to-make-his-mourning-mother-an-art-world-star-today-she-is-a-highlight-at-a-major-exhibition-in-london-180988808/</link><description>詹姆斯·麦克尼尔·惠斯勒 (James McNeill Whistler) 为其母亲创作的坚忍肖像画的正式名称为“灰黑编排第一号”，它定义了艺术家的风格和遗产。这件艺术品目前正在 150 多年前创作的同一座城市展出</description><pubDate>Tue, 26 May 2026 17:56:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/whistler-didnt-mean-to-make-his-mourning-mother-an-art-world-star-today-she-is-a-highlight-at-a-major-exhibition-in-london-180988808/</guid></item><item><title>一项新研究表明，人类的存在——不仅仅是我们对土地的改变——就能改变野生动物的行为</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-mere-presence-of-humans-not-just-our-changes-to-the-land-can-alter-wild-animals-behaviors-a-new-study-suggests-180988793/</link><description>研究人员检查了代表 37 个物种的数千只动物的 GPS 跟踪数据，以及 2020 年、Covid-19 封锁年份和前一年的匿名手机位置数据</description><pubDate>Tue, 26 May 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-mere-presence-of-humans-not-just-our-changes-to-the-land-can-alter-wild-animals-behaviors-a-new-study-suggests-180988793/</guid></item></channel></rss>